WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:07.674 --> 00:00:09.885
[Theme music playing]

2
00:00:11.000 --> 00:00:17.074
Do you want subtitles for any video?
-=[ ai.OpenSubtitles.com ]=-

3
00:01:48.650 --> 00:01:50.152
[Waves splashing]

4
00:01:51.361 --> 00:01:53.363
[Solemn instrumental music playing]

5
00:02:13.258 --> 00:02:14.259
[Man speaking valyrian]

6
00:03:19.658 --> 00:03:20.659
[Chuckles]

7
00:03:57.404 --> 00:03:59.489
[Solemn music continues]

8
00:04:27.476 --> 00:04:28.643
[Indistinct chatter]

9
00:04:57.088 --> 00:04:58.648
[In English] Have you seen your father?

10
00:05:01.009 --> 00:05:02.719
Your little cousins
have lost their mother.

11
00:05:04.012 --> 00:05:05.597
They could use a kind word.

12
00:05:05.680 --> 00:05:07.599
I have an equal claim to sympathy.

13
00:05:07.682 --> 00:05:09.434
- Jace.
- We should be at harrenhal.

14
00:05:09.518 --> 00:05:11.478
mourning lord lyonel and ser hannin.

15
00:05:12.771 --> 00:05:14.815
It would not be appropriate.

16
00:05:16.066 --> 00:05:19.110
The velaryons are our kin
and the strongs are not.

17
00:05:20.445 --> 00:05:21.655
Look at me.

18
00:05:22.364 --> 00:05:23.406
Do you understand?

19
00:05:52.519 --> 00:05:54.104
[Helaena] Hand turns loom.

20
00:05:54.187 --> 00:05:56.106
spool of green. spool of black.

21
00:05:56.189 --> 00:05:58.316
dragons of flesh

22
00:05:58.400 --> 00:06:00.235
weaving dragons of thread.

23
00:06:01.236 --> 00:06:04.489
Hand turns loom. spool of green...

24
00:06:04.573 --> 00:06:07.868
- We have nothing in common.
- She's our sister.

25
00:06:07.951 --> 00:06:10.537
- You marry her. then.
- I would perform my duty.

26
00:06:10.620 --> 00:06:13.290
- if mother had only betrothed us.
- If only.

27
00:06:13.373 --> 00:06:14.958
It would strengthen the family.

28
00:06:15.041 --> 00:06:16.793
Keep our valyrian blood pure.

29
00:06:16.877 --> 00:06:19.546
- She's an idiot.
- She's your future queen.

30
00:06:21.882 --> 00:06:24.092
We actually do have

31
00:06:24.968 --> 00:06:26.553
one thing in common.

32
00:06:26.636 --> 00:06:30.265
We both fancy creatures
with very long legs.

33
00:06:32.767 --> 00:06:33.810
Vvench!

34
00:06:34.519 --> 00:06:36.354
- Another!
- Aegon.

35
00:06:37.522 --> 00:06:40.400
Dragon's flesh.
weaving dragons of thread.

36
00:06:43.612 --> 00:06:45.614
[Music playing]

37
00:06:49.409 --> 00:06:51.369
Lyonel strong's son's
been staring at you

38
00:06:51.453 --> 00:06:53.053
since the moment we arrived. your grace.

39
00:06:57.125 --> 00:06:58.209
Unabashedly.

40
00:07:00.170 --> 00:07:02.255
It is only a look of pride. ser criston.

41
00:07:03.632 --> 00:07:05.258
Larys is the new lord of harrenhal.

42
00:07:41.044 --> 00:07:42.837
[Corlys] Both my seat and high tide

43
00:07:42.921 --> 00:07:44.839
will be yours one day. lucerys.

44
00:07:46.049 --> 00:07:48.009
Your brother will be king. of course.

45
00:07:49.427 --> 00:07:51.846
He'll sit on endless
councils and ceremonies.

46
00:07:51.930 --> 00:07:54.015
but lord of the tides rules the sea.

47
00:07:55.809 --> 00:07:56.810
[Lucerys] Sorry.

48
00:07:56.893 --> 00:07:58.061
I don't want it.

49
00:08:02.023 --> 00:08:03.358
It's your birthright. lad.

50
00:08:08.238 --> 00:08:11.408
If I'm the lord of driftmark.
it means everyone's dead.

51
00:08:18.707 --> 00:08:21.501
- I'm very sorry. my Princess.
- Thank you. Thank you.

52
00:08:45.275 --> 00:08:46.317
[Rhaena] Grandma...

53
00:08:51.072 --> 00:08:52.991
I don't want mother to be gone.

54
00:09:30.945 --> 00:09:32.947
[Dragon roaring]

55
00:09:42.791 --> 00:09:44.793
[Somber music playing]

56
00:10:07.273 --> 00:10:08.858
Retrieve your patron.

57
00:10:12.028 --> 00:10:13.029
Brother.

58
00:10:54.821 --> 00:10:57.115
Your girls are the very
image of their mother.

59
00:10:58.616 --> 00:11:00.660
A comfort and an anguish.

60
00:11:00.743 --> 00:11:02.120
as I well remember.

61
00:11:03.663 --> 00:11:04.873
The gods can be cruel.

62
00:11:07.876 --> 00:11:10.003
It seems they've been
especially cruel to you.

63
00:11:11.171 --> 00:11:12.172
[Chuckles softly]

64
00:11:12.255 --> 00:11:13.256
Yes.

65
00:11:27.854 --> 00:11:29.606
You should return with us
to king's landing.

66
00:11:30.565 --> 00:11:32.108
It's time that you came home.

67
00:11:32.192 --> 00:11:33.610
[Prince daemon]
Pentos is my home...

68
00:11:35.153 --> 00:11:37.280
- And that of my children.
- Daemon...

69
00:11:38.656 --> 00:11:40.408
I know we've had our differences.

70
00:11:41.326 --> 00:11:42.952
but let them pass with the years.

71
00:11:44.871 --> 00:11:46.706
There's a place for you in my court

72
00:11:46.789 --> 00:11:48.333
if that's something you should need.

73
00:11:48.416 --> 00:11:51.044
I need nothing.

74
00:12:00.720 --> 00:12:01.721
Brother.

75
00:12:06.809 --> 00:12:08.770
I'm sorry for your loss. my prince.

76
00:12:09.896 --> 00:12:13.441
No matter how fat the leech grows.
it always wants for another meal.

77
00:12:18.071 --> 00:12:20.073
[Solemn music continues]

78
00:12:24.702 --> 00:12:25.828
Go to bed.

79
00:12:25.912 --> 00:12:27.664
- But. mother...
- Go to bed.

80
00:12:39.092 --> 00:12:40.343
I'm going to bed. aemma.

81
00:12:42.428 --> 00:12:44.639
Shall I see after queen alicent.
your grace?

82
00:12:48.810 --> 00:12:50.270
No. ser harrold.

83
00:12:50.353 --> 00:12:52.313
[Harrold]
You have the night's watch. ser criston.

84
00:12:54.565 --> 00:12:55.775
Lord commander.

85
00:13:27.932 --> 00:13:29.475
[Gasping]

86
00:13:29.559 --> 00:13:30.559
Brother?

87
00:13:36.607 --> 00:13:37.692
Get to bed.

88
00:13:48.453 --> 00:13:49.704
[Breath trembling]

89
00:14:04.719 --> 00:14:06.721
[Dragon roaring]

90
00:14:09.223 --> 00:14:11.225
[Captivating music playing]

91
00:14:26.824 --> 00:14:28.826
[Dragon roaring]

92
00:14:39.670 --> 00:14:41.310
[Rhaenys velaryon]
She wanted to come home

93
00:14:42.006 --> 00:14:43.508
and he denied her.

94
00:14:45.134 --> 00:14:46.928
[Corlys] Daemon did
what he thought best.

95
00:14:49.347 --> 00:14:52.058
[Rhaenys velaryon] Daemon only ever does
what is best for daemon.

96
00:14:53.601 --> 00:14:55.395
Laena needed our maesters.

97
00:14:56.813 --> 00:14:58.398
[Corlys sighs]

98
00:15:01.067 --> 00:15:03.611
The surgeons in pentos
are as well-trained

99
00:15:03.694 --> 00:15:05.029
as our maesters.

100
00:15:09.242 --> 00:15:13.621
You are looking to place blame
for an act of the gods.

101
00:15:15.832 --> 00:15:17.875
Mayhaps the gods have scorned us...

102
00:15:19.544 --> 00:15:22.463
For our insatiable pride.

103
00:15:28.553 --> 00:15:30.346
The crown was yours

104
00:15:30.430 --> 00:15:34.809
until those fools at the great council
plucked it from your head.

105
00:15:37.478 --> 00:15:41.232
Is it such a terrible thing
for your husband to wish to win it back?

106
00:15:41.315 --> 00:15:44.026
Tonight of all nights.
let us lay aside this falsehood.

107
00:15:48.030 --> 00:15:49.949
It is notjustice for
your wife that drives you.

108
00:15:50.032 --> 00:15:51.701
It is your own ambition.

109
00:15:52.535 --> 00:15:54.203
'Tis desire for the throne.

110
00:15:54.287 --> 00:15:56.998
if not for yourself.
then for the scions of your house.

111
00:15:57.832 --> 00:16:00.460
I gave up the idea of wearing a crown
a generation ago.

112
00:16:00.543 --> 00:16:03.546
It is you. lord husband.
who refuses to abandon this pursuit.

113
00:16:03.629 --> 00:16:05.631
even now. at the cost of our children.

114
00:16:21.689 --> 00:16:23.524
What is this brief mortal life...

115
00:16:25.276 --> 00:16:27.111
If not the pursuit of legacy?

116
00:16:27.195 --> 00:16:30.031
Legacy may be why you
live your life. corlys.

117
00:16:41.459 --> 00:16:44.378
I want driftmark to pass through
laena's line to baela.

118
00:16:47.048 --> 00:16:48.549
To true velaryon blood.

119
00:16:50.635 --> 00:16:52.355
Declare it now.
while all are gathered here.

120
00:16:52.428 --> 00:16:54.680
and we will say that is how
we will honor laena's memory.

121
00:16:54.764 --> 00:16:56.390
And disinherit our son?

122
00:16:57.099 --> 00:16:58.939
[Rhaenys velaryon]
He will be the king consort.

123
00:16:59.018 --> 00:17:01.395
His son will one day
sit the iron throne.

124
00:17:01.479 --> 00:17:04.023
You would have me cast
an even darker shadow

125
00:17:04.106 --> 00:17:06.108
over those little boys
than already exists.

126
00:17:06.192 --> 00:17:07.401
We are alone here. husband.

127
00:17:07.485 --> 00:17:10.279
You can speak the plain truth
as we both know it.

128
00:17:17.787 --> 00:17:19.997
Rhaenyra's children
are not of your blood.

129
00:17:27.838 --> 00:17:29.340
But laena's are.

130
00:17:33.261 --> 00:17:34.762
They are her legacy.

131
00:17:36.264 --> 00:17:39.475
History does not remember blood.

132
00:17:44.730 --> 00:17:46.274
It remembers names.

133
00:18:08.004 --> 00:18:10.464
[Rhaenyra]
Laenor has been restless for years.

134
00:18:10.548 --> 00:18:14.218
but now. he will be useless.

135
00:18:15.052 --> 00:18:16.052
Or worse.

136
00:18:18.931 --> 00:18:21.726
I know better than anyone
that our marriage is a farce.

137
00:18:23.019 --> 00:18:26.397
But I at least make the effort
to maintain appearances.

138
00:18:28.065 --> 00:18:29.317
You have more to lose.

139
00:18:30.901 --> 00:18:33.696
Yes. well. that has been
my lot since my father named me heir.

140
00:18:37.158 --> 00:18:38.284
We did try...

141
00:18:40.411 --> 00:18:41.912
To conceive a child.

142
00:18:41.996 --> 00:18:45.708
We performed our duty as best we could.

143
00:18:48.711 --> 00:18:50.046
But to no avail.

144
00:18:57.470 --> 00:18:58.763
There was no joy in it.

145
00:19:03.434 --> 00:19:04.727
I found that elsewhere.

146
00:19:08.439 --> 00:19:10.816
- It felt good to be desired.
- Mmm.

147
00:19:13.527 --> 00:19:15.863
I understand ser hannin was quite...

148
00:19:18.324 --> 00:19:19.492
Devoted to you.

149
00:19:22.286 --> 00:19:23.412
Yes. he was.

150
00:19:25.623 --> 00:19:26.916
And I trusted him.

151
00:19:32.463 --> 00:19:35.299
Should've forbidden ser hannin
from returning to the riverlands.

152
00:19:37.343 --> 00:19:39.387
Harren's curse
is said to be as strong now

153
00:19:39.470 --> 00:19:40.630
as it was after the conquest.

154
00:19:40.680 --> 00:19:41.680
That's a ghost story.

155
00:19:42.264 --> 00:19:44.850
one ser Otto and the queen
would gladly exploit.

156
00:19:45.559 --> 00:19:48.979
I do not believe alicent
capable of cold murder.

157
00:19:53.401 --> 00:19:55.486
Each of us is capable of depravity.

158
00:19:57.571 --> 00:19:59.115
And more than you would believe.

159
00:20:02.993 --> 00:20:04.328
I believe it of you.

160
00:20:07.248 --> 00:20:08.874
If you're accusing me of some depravity.

161
00:20:08.958 --> 00:20:10.334
you'll need to be more specific.

162
00:20:13.129 --> 00:20:14.338
[Rhaenyra] I've been alone.

163
00:20:16.215 --> 00:20:18.551
- You abandoned me.
- [Prince daemon] I spared you.

164
00:20:18.634 --> 00:20:20.344
- You were a child.
- [Rhaenyra] Yes.

165
00:20:21.137 --> 00:20:23.013
Yes. I was a child.

166
00:20:23.097 --> 00:20:24.849
And look at what my life
became without you.

167
00:20:27.393 --> 00:20:29.019
Droll tragedy.

168
00:20:29.103 --> 00:20:31.105
And iwonder what you
think of mine by comparison?

169
00:20:32.064 --> 00:20:33.274
I know little of it.

170
00:20:39.488 --> 00:20:40.531
Did you love her?

171
00:20:43.701 --> 00:20:44.952
We were happy enough.

172
00:20:46.787 --> 00:20:49.206
Well. that in itself
is a great achievement.

173
00:20:55.421 --> 00:20:57.047
- I am sorry.
- Don't be.

174
00:20:59.508 --> 00:21:01.594
I am at least allowed
to mourn my losses.

175
00:21:10.060 --> 00:21:11.145
[Sighs]

176
00:21:25.451 --> 00:21:27.077
[Music playing]

177
00:21:32.500 --> 00:21:33.542
Rhaenyra.

178
00:21:39.131 --> 00:21:40.466
I'm no longer a child.

179
00:22:01.195 --> 00:22:02.530
[Whispers] I want you.

180
00:22:19.213 --> 00:22:21.215
[Music continues]

181
00:23:16.228 --> 00:23:17.563
[Breathing heavily]

182
00:23:53.265 --> 00:23:55.267
[Wind blowing]

183
00:24:22.628 --> 00:24:24.254
[Panting]

184
00:25:04.503 --> 00:25:05.503
Fuck.

185
00:25:12.219 --> 00:25:14.221
[Dragon snoring]

186
00:25:33.949 --> 00:25:35.576
[Birds screeching]

187
00:25:47.129 --> 00:25:49.548
[Dragon continues snoring]

188
00:26:04.772 --> 00:26:05.898
[Growling]

189
00:26:14.990 --> 00:26:16.492
[Sniffing]

190
00:26:22.623 --> 00:26:24.124
[Dragon snoring]

191
00:26:24.208 --> 00:26:25.834
[Breathing heavily]

192
00:26:29.588 --> 00:26:31.215
[Growling]

193
00:26:33.884 --> 00:26:34.924
[Aemond speaking valyrian]

194
00:26:34.968 --> 00:26:36.136
Dohaeras!

195
00:26:37.596 --> 00:26:40.891
Dohaeras. vhagar! Lykiri!

196
00:26:42.142 --> 00:26:43.142
I ykiri!

197
00:26:48.482 --> 00:26:49.483
I ykiri.

198
00:26:54.822 --> 00:26:56.448
[Low growl]

199
00:27:08.919 --> 00:27:10.921
[Suspenseful music playing]

200
00:27:11.004 --> 00:27:12.422
[Panting]

201
00:27:15.634 --> 00:27:16.635
[Grunts]

202
00:27:30.149 --> 00:27:31.567
[Growling]

203
00:27:38.240 --> 00:27:39.241
Soves!

204
00:27:42.870 --> 00:27:46.373
Dohaeras. vhagar! Soves!

205
00:27:49.042 --> 00:27:50.377
[Dramatic music playing]

206
00:27:55.883 --> 00:27:57.134
[Screaming]

207
00:27:57.217 --> 00:27:58.385
[Roaring]

208
00:28:15.027 --> 00:28:17.029
[Aemond screaming]

209
00:28:32.002 --> 00:28:33.003
[Continues screaming]

210
00:28:42.763 --> 00:28:44.139
[Screaming]

211
00:28:50.771 --> 00:28:52.564
[Sweeping music playing]

212
00:28:59.071 --> 00:29:01.073
- [Birds screeching]
- [Aemond grunting]

213
00:29:17.256 --> 00:29:18.340
[Screaming]

214
00:29:36.108 --> 00:29:37.693
Yeah! [Laughs]

215
00:29:47.411 --> 00:29:48.578
[Grunts]

216
00:30:01.216 --> 00:30:03.051
Jace. Jace.

217
00:30:03.135 --> 00:30:05.178
Jace. wake up. Wake up.

218
00:30:07.514 --> 00:30:10.559
- Someone stole vhagar.
- What?

219
00:30:21.361 --> 00:30:23.363
[Dragon roaring in distance]

220
00:30:30.412 --> 00:30:31.413
Who is it?

221
00:30:56.063 --> 00:30:58.148
Jace. what are we doing?

222
00:30:58.231 --> 00:31:00.192
- It's him.
- It's me.

223
00:31:00.275 --> 00:31:03.111
- Vhagar is my mother's dragon.
- [Aemond] Your mother's dead.

224
00:31:03.779 --> 00:31:06.073
- And vhagar has a new rider now.
- She was mine to claim.

225
00:31:06.156 --> 00:31:07.783
[Aemond] Then you should've claimed her!

226
00:31:07.866 --> 00:31:09.910
Maybe your cousins
can find you a pig to ride.

227
00:31:10.494 --> 00:31:11.953
It would suit you.

228
00:31:12.037 --> 00:31:13.037
[Yells]

229
00:31:14.039 --> 00:31:15.374
[Both grunting]

230
00:31:17.501 --> 00:31:19.586
Come at me again
and I'll feed you to my dragon!

231
00:31:19.669 --> 00:31:20.669
[Yells]

232
00:31:24.591 --> 00:31:25.592
[Screams]

233
00:31:25.675 --> 00:31:26.676
[Groans]

234
00:31:29.262 --> 00:31:30.555
[All grunting]

235
00:31:51.118 --> 00:31:54.871
You will die screaming in flames
just as your father did!

236
00:31:54.955 --> 00:31:56.123
Bastards.

237
00:31:56.206 --> 00:31:57.916
My father's still alive.

238
00:31:58.792 --> 00:32:01.795
He doesn't know. does he. lord strong?

239
00:32:03.839 --> 00:32:04.839
Jace!

240
00:32:08.051 --> 00:32:09.052
[Jacaerys groans]

241
00:32:21.064 --> 00:32:22.065
[Screaming]

242
00:32:25.110 --> 00:32:26.445
[Harrold] Cease this at once!

243
00:32:26.528 --> 00:32:27.529
[Wailing]

244
00:32:27.946 --> 00:32:28.946
[Harrold] Get away!

245
00:32:31.741 --> 00:32:34.202
My prince. my prince. Let me see.

246
00:32:38.373 --> 00:32:39.666
Gods be good.

247
00:32:41.460 --> 00:32:43.670
How could you allow
such a thing to happen?

248
00:32:46.590 --> 00:32:48.049
I will have answers.

249
00:32:48.133 --> 00:32:50.385
[Harrold] The princes were supposed
to be Abed. my king.

250
00:32:51.470 --> 00:32:52.670
[Viserys I] Who had the watch?

251
00:32:53.555 --> 00:32:56.195
[Criston] Young prince was attacked by
his own cousins. your grace.

252
00:32:56.266 --> 00:33:00.604
You swore oaths to protect
and defend my blood!

253
00:33:00.687 --> 00:33:02.081
[Harrold] I'm very sorry. your grace.

254
00:33:02.105 --> 00:33:04.417
[Criston] The kingsguard has never had
to defend princes from princes.

255
00:33:04.441 --> 00:33:06.401
- your grace.
- That is no answer!

256
00:33:06.485 --> 00:33:08.737
It will heal. will it not. maester?

257
00:33:10.947 --> 00:33:12.240
[Maester] The flesh will heal.

258
00:33:15.327 --> 00:33:16.912
But the eye is lost. your grace.

259
00:33:19.915 --> 00:33:21.635
- [Alicent] Where were you?
- [Aegon ii] Me?

260
00:33:22.167 --> 00:33:24.044
- Ow! What was that for?
- That was nothing

261
00:33:24.127 --> 00:33:25.879
compared to the abuse
your brother suffered

262
00:33:25.962 --> 00:33:27.881
while you were drowning
in your cups. you fool.

263
00:33:27.964 --> 00:33:30.091
- [Door opens]
- [Corlys] What is the meaning of this?

264
00:33:30.175 --> 00:33:32.636
[Rhaenys velaryon] Baela. rhaena!
What happened?

265
00:33:32.719 --> 00:33:34.012
What happened?

266
00:33:38.600 --> 00:33:39.643
Jace?

267
00:33:40.810 --> 00:33:41.853
Luke!

268
00:33:43.813 --> 00:33:45.982
- Show me. Show me.
- [Groaning]

269
00:33:46.066 --> 00:33:47.776
- Who did this?
- They attacked me!

270
00:33:47.859 --> 00:33:50.111
- He attacked baela!
- He broke Luke's nose!

271
00:33:50.195 --> 00:33:51.530
[Children shouting]

272
00:33:55.367 --> 00:33:56.807
[Baela] He stole my mother's dragon!

273
00:33:57.786 --> 00:33:59.546
- Enough.
- [Lucerys] He was gonna kill Jace!

274
00:33:59.579 --> 00:34:00.914
- I didn't do anything!
- Enoughn

275
00:34:00.997 --> 00:34:02.266
it should be my son telling the tale!

276
00:34:02.290 --> 00:34:03.792
- He called us...
- Silence!

277
00:34:07.796 --> 00:34:09.506
[Whispers] He called us bastards.

278
00:34:16.429 --> 00:34:17.722
[Viserys I] Aemond...

279
00:34:18.348 --> 00:34:20.267
I will have the truth of what happened.

280
00:34:22.352 --> 00:34:24.396
- Now.
- What else is there to hear?

281
00:34:24.479 --> 00:34:26.606
Your son has been maimed.
Her son is responsible.

282
00:34:26.690 --> 00:34:28.793
- It was a regrettable accident.
- [Alicent] Accident?

283
00:34:28.817 --> 00:34:31.069
The prince lucerys brought
a blade to the ambush.

284
00:34:31.152 --> 00:34:32.487
He meant to kill my son.

285
00:34:32.571 --> 00:34:35.323
It was my sons who were attacked

286
00:34:35.407 --> 00:34:37.117
and forced to defend themselves.

287
00:34:38.118 --> 00:34:40.829
Vile insults were levied against them.

288
00:34:40.912 --> 00:34:41.997
What insults?

289
00:34:46.293 --> 00:34:49.504
The legitimacy of my sons' birth
was put loudly to question.

290
00:34:49.588 --> 00:34:51.798
- What?
- He called us bastards.

291
00:34:56.761 --> 00:35:01.641
[Rhaenyra] My sons are in line
to inherit the iron throne. your grace.

292
00:35:01.725 --> 00:35:03.226
This is the highest of treasons.

293
00:35:05.437 --> 00:35:07.522
Prince aemond must be sharply questioned

294
00:35:07.606 --> 00:35:09.941
so we might learn where
he heard such slanders.

295
00:35:11.901 --> 00:35:12.986
Over an insult?

296
00:35:14.446 --> 00:35:16.781
My son has lost an eye.

297
00:35:19.242 --> 00:35:22.287
You tell me. boy.
Where did you hear this lie?

298
00:35:22.370 --> 00:35:24.015
[Alicent] The insult
was training yard bluster.

299
00:35:24.039 --> 00:35:25.839
- The lot of boys. It was nothing.
- Aemond...

300
00:35:26.499 --> 00:35:27.667
I asked you a question.

301
00:35:31.212 --> 00:35:34.257
Where is ser laenor. I wonder?
The boys' father?

302
00:35:34.341 --> 00:35:36.319
Perhaps he might have
something to say in the matter.

303
00:35:36.343 --> 00:35:37.823
[Viserys I] Yes. Where is ser laenor?

304
00:35:38.845 --> 00:35:42.265
I do not know. your grace.
I... could not find sleep.

305
00:35:42.349 --> 00:35:43.808
I had gone out to walk.

306
00:35:44.559 --> 00:35:46.853
Entertaining his young squires.
I would venture.

307
00:35:50.857 --> 00:35:52.025
[Viserys I] Aemond...

308
00:35:53.526 --> 00:35:54.694
Look at me.

309
00:35:57.072 --> 00:35:58.573
Your king demands an answer.

310
00:35:59.199 --> 00:36:00.909
Who spoke these lies to you?

311
00:36:02.619 --> 00:36:04.454
[Suspenseful music playing]

312
00:36:06.790 --> 00:36:08.208
[Breath trembling]

313
00:36:18.968 --> 00:36:20.178
It was aegon.

314
00:36:26.559 --> 00:36:28.895
And you. boy?

315
00:36:31.731 --> 00:36:33.733
Where did you hear such calumnies?

316
00:36:35.110 --> 00:36:38.530
Aegon! Tell me the truth of it!

317
00:36:40.448 --> 00:36:42.450
We know. father.

318
00:36:44.744 --> 00:36:46.955
Everyone knows.

319
00:36:48.081 --> 00:36:49.416
Just look at them.

320
00:36:52.585 --> 00:36:54.587
[Music continues]

321
00:37:06.933 --> 00:37:09.394
This interminable infighting must cease!

322
00:37:10.145 --> 00:37:11.354
All of you!

323
00:37:14.190 --> 00:37:15.525
We are family!

324
00:37:20.697 --> 00:37:23.533
Now make your apologies
and show good will to one another.

325
00:37:24.784 --> 00:37:28.538
Your father. your grandsire.
your king demands it!

326
00:37:43.970 --> 00:37:45.138
That is insufficient.

327
00:37:48.433 --> 00:37:50.810
Aemond has been damaged.
permanently. my king.

328
00:37:50.894 --> 00:37:52.312
"Good will" cannot make him whole.

329
00:37:52.395 --> 00:37:56.107
I know. alicent.
but I cannot restore his eye.

330
00:37:56.191 --> 00:37:57.817
No. because it's been taken.

331
00:37:57.901 --> 00:38:00.987
- What would you have me do?
- There is a debt to be paid.

332
00:38:04.866 --> 00:38:06.626
I shall have one of her
son's eyes in return.

333
00:38:08.036 --> 00:38:09.996
[People gasping]

334
00:38:11.080 --> 00:38:13.666
- My dear wife.
- He is your son. viserys.

335
00:38:13.833 --> 00:38:14.833
Your blood.

336
00:38:15.376 --> 00:38:19.714
Do not... allow your temper
to guide your judgment.

337
00:38:25.845 --> 00:38:28.165
[Alicent] If the king will not
seekjustice. the queen will.

338
00:38:28.973 --> 00:38:29.974
Ser criston...

339
00:38:31.351 --> 00:38:33.353
Bring me the eye of lucerys velaryon.

340
00:38:34.187 --> 00:38:35.688
- Mother!
- [Viserys I] Alicent.

341
00:38:35.772 --> 00:38:38.459
He can choose which eye to keep.
a privilege he did not Grant my son.

342
00:38:38.483 --> 00:38:39.901
You will do no such thing.

343
00:38:39.984 --> 00:38:42.070
- Stay your hand.
- No. you are sworn to me!

344
00:38:47.200 --> 00:38:48.701
As your protector. my queen.

345
00:38:52.205 --> 00:38:56.251
Alicent. this matter... is finished.

346
00:38:57.293 --> 00:38:58.419
Do you understand?

347
00:39:10.181 --> 00:39:11.224
And let it be known.

348
00:39:12.100 --> 00:39:13.940
anyone whose tongue dares
to question the birth

349
00:39:14.018 --> 00:39:15.353
of Princess rhaenyra's sons

350
00:39:16.229 --> 00:39:17.647
should have it removed.

351
00:39:21.276 --> 00:39:22.402
Thank you. father.

352
00:39:33.621 --> 00:39:35.540
- Your grace. Stay with the king!
- Alicent!

353
00:39:35.623 --> 00:39:37.125
[Man] Hold your approach!

354
00:39:37.208 --> 00:39:39.061
- [Harrold] Do not. ser criston!
- [Viserys I] Alicent!

355
00:39:39.085 --> 00:39:40.837
- [Screaming]
- Do not. ser criston!

356
00:39:40.920 --> 00:39:41.920
[Viserys I] Alicent!

357
00:39:42.672 --> 00:39:43.672
[Rhaenyra] No!

358
00:39:45.174 --> 00:39:46.414
[Harrold] Stay your hand. Cole!

359
00:39:48.511 --> 00:39:50.847
- You've gone too far.
- I?

360
00:39:51.514 --> 00:39:53.600
What have I done but
what was expected of me?

361
00:39:54.767 --> 00:39:58.271
Forever upholding the kingdom.
the family. the law.

362
00:40:00.023 --> 00:40:01.703
While you flout it all
to do as you please.

363
00:40:01.733 --> 00:40:02.901
Alicent. let her go!

364
00:40:02.984 --> 00:40:05.236
Where is duty? Where is sacrifice?

365
00:40:05.320 --> 00:40:07.614
It's trampled under
your pretty foot again.

366
00:40:07.697 --> 00:40:09.365
Release the blade. alicent.

367
00:40:10.033 --> 00:40:11.701
And now you take my son's eye.

368
00:40:11.784 --> 00:40:13.578
and to even that. you feel entitled.

369
00:40:13.661 --> 00:40:15.121
Exhausting. wasn't it?

370
00:40:15.997 --> 00:40:18.541
Hiding beneath the cloak
of your own righteousness.

371
00:40:19.876 --> 00:40:22.587
[Softly] But now they see you
as you are.

372
00:40:22.670 --> 00:40:23.755
[Grunts]

373
00:40:32.972 --> 00:40:34.390
[Tense music playing]

374
00:40:49.822 --> 00:40:50.907
[Breath trembling]

375
00:41:00.625 --> 00:41:01.834
Do not mourn me. mother.

376
00:41:02.752 --> 00:41:03.920
It was a fair exchange.

377
00:41:05.672 --> 00:41:07.131
I may have lost an eye...

378
00:41:09.133 --> 00:41:10.301
But I gained a dragon.

379
00:41:19.435 --> 00:41:21.062
This proceeding is at an end.

380
00:41:22.772 --> 00:41:23.773
[Straining]

381
00:41:59.642 --> 00:42:00.643
The hand. your grace.

382
00:42:01.436 --> 00:42:03.062
[Footsteps approaching]

383
00:42:17.201 --> 00:42:18.411
[Door closes]

384
00:42:18.494 --> 00:42:19.495
[Alicent] Say your piece.

385
00:42:20.371 --> 00:42:21.998
Now. what piece is that?

386
00:42:25.668 --> 00:42:27.253
I've conducted myself in a manner...

387
00:42:28.379 --> 00:42:29.964
Unbefitting my station.

388
00:42:32.050 --> 00:42:33.217
Or any other.

389
00:42:36.846 --> 00:42:38.139
I lost composure.

390
00:42:40.433 --> 00:42:41.517
assaulted the Princess.

391
00:42:44.312 --> 00:42:45.605
Already the word is spreading.

392
00:42:45.688 --> 00:42:47.440
the gossip speculating
that I've gone mad.

393
00:42:49.567 --> 00:42:50.568
All true.

394
00:42:51.235 --> 00:42:52.403
I disgraced myself.

395
00:42:54.989 --> 00:42:57.617
And ensured my husband's favor
will forever rest on her.

396
00:43:00.286 --> 00:43:01.537
And yet...

397
00:43:03.206 --> 00:43:06.000
I've never seen that side of you.
my daughter.

398
00:43:09.045 --> 00:43:10.505
I even doubted its existence.

399
00:43:10.588 --> 00:43:13.758
- It was an ugly thing. I regret it.
- We play an ugly game.

400
00:43:16.219 --> 00:43:17.595
And now. for the first time.

401
00:43:17.678 --> 00:43:20.431
I see that you have
the determination to win it.

402
00:43:24.769 --> 00:43:26.938
- Rhaenyra...
- [Otto] You see her for what she is.

403
00:43:28.106 --> 00:43:30.274
What the king's stubbornness
has wrought.

404
00:43:35.071 --> 00:43:37.156
- What will he say to me?
- [Otto] He'll forgive you.

405
00:43:39.659 --> 00:43:40.785
What else can he do?

406
00:43:42.495 --> 00:43:44.747
Now go to him. be penitent.

407
00:43:45.373 --> 00:43:46.999
plead the injury to your son.

408
00:43:48.126 --> 00:43:49.418
Keep a grip on your passions.

409
00:43:50.962 --> 00:43:54.507
And I promise you. in time.
you and I together will prevail.

410
00:43:58.261 --> 00:44:00.346
What that rogue aemond has done

411
00:44:00.429 --> 00:44:02.431
in winning vhagar to our side.

412
00:44:04.892 --> 00:44:06.561
The boy was right.

413
00:44:06.644 --> 00:44:09.230
It's worth a thousand times
the price he paid.

414
00:44:23.494 --> 00:44:24.662
[Rhaenyra straining]

415
00:44:33.796 --> 00:44:34.964
[Groans softly]

416
00:44:37.008 --> 00:44:40.011
You will scar. but the wound will heal.

417
00:44:41.512 --> 00:44:43.472
Valyrian steel cuts clean.

418
00:44:44.348 --> 00:44:45.433
[Door opens]

419
00:44:51.564 --> 00:44:52.565
Gods.

420
00:44:54.734 --> 00:44:55.985
[Laenor] Ls everyone all right?

421
00:44:56.611 --> 00:44:58.196
[Maester] A broken nose is the worst.

422
00:44:58.279 --> 00:44:59.479
[Rhaenyra] Thank you. maester.

423
00:45:00.281 --> 00:45:01.324
Leave us.

424
00:45:05.620 --> 00:45:06.620
You as well.

425
00:45:07.371 --> 00:45:09.248
You've already found
enough trouble today.

426
00:45:10.208 --> 00:45:11.208
Yes. mother.

427
00:45:18.299 --> 00:45:19.383
[Door closes]

428
00:45:19.467 --> 00:45:20.968
[Laenor] I should've been there.

429
00:45:21.052 --> 00:45:22.553
Those should be our house words.

430
00:45:26.057 --> 00:45:28.643
I have fought dreadful enemies.

431
00:45:28.726 --> 00:45:30.937
but I could not defend my dear sister

432
00:45:31.687 --> 00:45:33.314
far from home and in agony.

433
00:45:35.191 --> 00:45:37.735
- I could not defend you.
- Sit down.

434
00:45:49.038 --> 00:45:50.957
Aemond called our sons bastards.

435
00:45:58.047 --> 00:45:59.840
I have failed you. rhaenyra.

436
00:46:00.716 --> 00:46:01.716
Our marriage...

437
00:46:03.552 --> 00:46:04.845
I tried.

438
00:46:07.056 --> 00:46:08.057
Our boys...

439
00:46:10.101 --> 00:46:11.644
- I do love them.
- I know.

440
00:46:11.727 --> 00:46:12.770
Deeply.

441
00:46:17.024 --> 00:46:18.359
But I have not. mayhaps...

442
00:46:20.569 --> 00:46:21.570
Loved them enough.

443
00:46:27.868 --> 00:46:29.745
I had hoped to bear your children.

444
00:46:32.164 --> 00:46:33.708
The few times we lay together.

445
00:46:37.878 --> 00:46:39.297
Things might've been different.

446
00:46:43.384 --> 00:46:46.220
I hate the gods
for making me as they did.

447
00:46:47.680 --> 00:46:48.806
I do not.

448
00:46:50.016 --> 00:46:51.600
You are an honorable man

449
00:46:52.685 --> 00:46:53.769
with a good heart.

450
00:46:55.938 --> 00:46:57.398
[Chuckles] It's a rare thing.

451
00:47:03.612 --> 00:47:05.948
[Laenor] We made an arrangement
all those years ago

452
00:47:06.032 --> 00:47:07.783
to do our duty and...

453
00:47:09.577 --> 00:47:11.037
Yet explore happiness.

454
00:47:11.829 --> 00:47:12.955
[Rhaenyra sighs]

455
00:47:13.956 --> 00:47:14.957
[Chuckles]

456
00:47:17.168 --> 00:47:18.169
[Sighs]

457
00:47:18.627 --> 00:47:20.713
- [Chuckles]
- [Laenor] But there are times

458
00:47:20.796 --> 00:47:23.841
I think when these things
cannot mutually exist.

459
00:47:27.136 --> 00:47:30.473
Ser qarl will return soon
to the fighting in the stepstones.

460
00:47:32.558 --> 00:47:34.643
But I recommit myself to you.

461
00:47:36.729 --> 00:47:40.900
And to strengthening our house
as we prepare you for your ascension.

462
00:47:40.983 --> 00:47:44.362
I will raise our sons
to be princes of the realm.

463
00:47:44.445 --> 00:47:45.630
- Laenor...
- You deserve better

464
00:47:45.654 --> 00:47:46.739
than what I have been.

465
00:47:46.822 --> 00:47:48.115
[Music playing]

466
00:47:49.742 --> 00:47:51.035
You deserve a husband.

467
00:48:02.630 --> 00:48:03.839
[Birds squawking]

468
00:48:06.258 --> 00:48:07.468
[Music continues]

469
00:48:11.972 --> 00:48:14.350
I've asked them to have wine ready
for you on the ship.

470
00:48:14.975 --> 00:48:16.227
To help you sleep.

471
00:48:20.606 --> 00:48:21.816
[Sighs wearily]

472
00:48:24.610 --> 00:48:25.653
I'm so sorry.

473
00:48:29.365 --> 00:48:30.365
Viserys...

474
00:48:30.408 --> 00:48:32.076
We will speak no more of it.

475
00:48:56.892 --> 00:48:58.894
[Dramatic music playing]

476
00:49:06.485 --> 00:49:07.903
[Roaring]

477
00:49:25.504 --> 00:49:26.922
[Music continues]

478
00:49:38.058 --> 00:49:40.478
[Dragon roaring]

479
00:49:48.444 --> 00:49:50.029
Fire is such strange power.

480
00:49:54.992 --> 00:49:57.828
Everything that house Targaryen
possesses is owed to it.

481
00:50:00.539 --> 00:50:02.917
Yet it has cost us both what we loved.

482
00:50:04.752 --> 00:50:06.587
Perhaps the velaryons
knew the truth of it.

483
00:50:06.670 --> 00:50:08.088
The sea is the better ally.

484
00:50:09.840 --> 00:50:11.008
Fire is a prison.

485
00:50:12.051 --> 00:50:14.094
The sea offers an escape.

486
00:50:23.812 --> 00:50:25.314
[Larys] A perversion of justice.

487
00:50:26.023 --> 00:50:27.107
The young prince...

488
00:50:28.108 --> 00:50:29.108
Defiled.

489
00:50:30.778 --> 00:50:32.071
An outrage.

490
00:50:34.073 --> 00:50:35.073
Indeed.

491
00:50:38.953 --> 00:50:42.957
If it's an eye you want to balance
the scales. I am your servant.

492
00:50:48.462 --> 00:50:50.381
That will not be necessary.

493
00:50:53.217 --> 00:50:55.135
But your devotion
has not gone unnoticed.

494
00:50:57.054 --> 00:50:58.347
These are dangerous times.

495
00:51:03.852 --> 00:51:06.272
The day will doubtless come
when I require such a friend.

496
00:51:08.399 --> 00:51:11.443
With not only skill
but discretion as well.

497
00:51:14.822 --> 00:51:17.700
I shall await your call. my queen.

498
00:51:34.049 --> 00:51:35.342
I need you. uncle.

499
00:51:40.931 --> 00:51:42.349
[Music playing]

500
00:51:45.019 --> 00:51:46.020
[Speaking valyrian]

501
00:52:38.405 --> 00:52:40.991
[In English] We could not marry
unless laenor were dead.

502
00:52:46.747 --> 00:52:47.748
I know.

503
00:52:47.831 --> 00:52:50.417
[Captivating music playing]

504
00:52:59.385 --> 00:53:00.594
[Indistinct chatter]

505
00:53:01.887 --> 00:53:04.515
I've heard about your exploits
in the stepstones.

506
00:53:05.516 --> 00:53:06.600
ser qarl.

507
00:53:07.518 --> 00:53:10.312
Said to be a knight of remarkable skill.

508
00:53:10.396 --> 00:53:11.480
You flatter me. m'lord.

509
00:53:12.272 --> 00:53:13.816
[Prince daemon] But alas. common-born.

510
00:53:15.067 --> 00:53:18.612
You're a landless knight
with a lord's taste.

511
00:53:18.904 --> 00:53:20.614
Ser laenor's been kind to me.

512
00:53:22.074 --> 00:53:23.075
Do you know...

513
00:53:26.120 --> 00:53:28.288
There are places
across the narrow sea...

514
00:53:29.790 --> 00:53:32.042
Where it doesn't matter
what a man's name is?

515
00:53:33.669 --> 00:53:35.546
Only how much gold he possesses.

516
00:53:39.758 --> 00:53:41.385
What are you asking of me. m'lord?

517
00:53:43.220 --> 00:53:44.263
A quick death.

518
00:53:45.639 --> 00:53:46.849
One with witnesses.

519
00:53:50.310 --> 00:53:51.729
[Music continues]

520
00:53:56.108 --> 00:53:57.735
[Rhaenyra] I will not be a tyrant.

521
00:53:59.069 --> 00:54:00.237
And rule through terror.

522
00:54:01.613 --> 00:54:03.699
[Prince daemon]
A tyrant rules only through terror.

523
